management

Class Entry

  • java.lang.Object
    • management.Entry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry

    public abstract class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the super class of several Entry related subclasses.

    Following extensions are related to this class: CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry.

    All extensions have at least two constructors. One for creating completely new data, that is going to be stored in the database, and one for storing already retrieved data.

    Entries are used to build Modules and fill them with content.

        Constructor that initializes the extensions of this class. (Overloaded)

        Following extensions may use this constructor: CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry

        This overloaded version is used to import already existing data. e.g. from the database.

        Parameters:
        version - The version of this Entry. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        date - The modification date. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        classification - Should this entry go to Dezernat 2 ? (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        approvalstatus - Is this entry already approved ? (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        declined - Is it declined and needs to be rewritten again ? (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        entryID - This entry's ID. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        title - The title of this entry. Used by the document creation as content title. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        order - The order of this entry. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        See Also:
        CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry

      • Entry

        public Entry(java.lang.String title,
     int order)
        Constructor that initializes the extensions of this class. (Overloaded)

        Following extensions may use this constructor: CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry

        This overloaded version is used when new data is going to be created. e.g. a new entry needs to be added to a module, or a completely new module is going to be created.

        Parameters:
        title - The title of this entry. Used by the document creation as content title. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        order - The order of this entry. (Used by extensions to initialize this super class)
        See Also:
        CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry
